# Breaking Down The URL Validation Regex!

In this tutorial, I will be breaking down the Regex (Regular Expression) that is used to validate URLs. A Regex is a sequence of characters that define a search pattern that can be used to validate user input.

## Summary

The following Regex is used to validate a URL!

/^(https?:\/\/)?([\da-z\.-]+)\.([a-z\.]{2,6})([\/\w \.-]*)*\/?$/



